Leadership Philosophy

Greg Dills

November 2020

About

The purpose of this document is to establish a basis for my personal views on what it takes to be a leader. I stand behind these values and principles and will hold myself accountable to these statements.

Expectations of Myself

I will:

  • Work Hard: We all have a role to play. I pride myself on taking my job seriously and performing effectively.
  • Be a Team Player: Working together maximizes the potential for growth and prosperity. We are all in this together!
  • Learn from my Mistakes: Making a mistake is inevitable. I will strive to better myself every step of the way.
  • Continue to Innovate: I will always be hungry to learn something new and to research and find the optimal solution.
  • Help Others: I enjoy helping others grow and learn.

Expectations of Others

I expect you to:

  • Be Honest: If there is an issue, let me know. We can work on it together.
  • Be Passionate about your work: Positivity and enthusiasim will go a long way!
  • Own your mistakes: We all make them and they will happen.
  • Ask for help: As a team, we need to support each other.
  • Be timely and accurate: It is critical to arrive on time (or early!).

Non-Negotiables

What matters most to me:

  • Treat others with dignity and respect
  • Maintain a healthy work-life balance
  • Maintain a positive attitude

My commitment

I will strive to be an effective leader, creating a fun, productive and stimulating work environment. I am open to new ideas and ways of thinking. I will never dismiss your ideas and will always follow-through. I will work hard, and create a positive atmosphere as often as possible!

Creativity Is Intelligence Having Fun. -Albert Einstein
